            <h1>Welcome!</h1> 
            <p>
             "You are invited to take part in a research study on predict the value of one mutual fund across several trials. In the following, we will describe the instructions including your rights and data collection rules of our experiments. " ==$0
             <i>
                 "This study has been reviewed and approved by the Department of Psychology Research Ethics Committee at the University of Warwick." ==$0
             </i>
            </p>
            <p>please take the time to read the following information carefully.</p>
        </div>
        <h3>Study Information</h3>
        <div class="briefing"> 
            <h4>What will happen?</h4>
            <p>
                "You will first try to guess the value of AAA for the initial 20 points with feedback and then predict an additional 20 points without feedback. The task will take about 15-20mins."
            </p>
            <h4>What are your rights?</h4>
            <p>
                "Your participation is completely voluntary. You can withdraw at any time, and for any reason, simply by closing your browser. You have the right to omit or refuse to answer the demographic questions. However, we are only able to pay you if you complete the survey. "
            </p>
            <h4>What data do we collect?</h4>
            <p>
                "No identifiable data will be collected from you as part of this study. This means that once your responses have been submitted to the research team, it will not be possible to withdraw this data as your individual responses cannot be identified. We only will record the predictions you submit and demographic information. "
            </p>
            <h4>What happen to your data?</h4>
            <p>
                "Data will be securely stored on University of Warwick computers and will be processed only for the purpose of scientific analysis.  Access to the data will be restricted to the investigator of research team: Adam Sanborn, Nick Chater, Jake Spicer, Pablo Leon-Villagra, LIN LI. "
            </p>
            <p> 
                "Further information can be found in the " <a href="https://warwick.ac.uk/services/idc/dataprotection/privacynotices/researchprivacynotice ">University's Privacy notice for research</a>
                ", or by contacting the Information and Data Compliance Team at "<a href="mailto:GDPR@warwick.ac.uk">.</a>
            </p>
            <p>
                "If you require further information, please contact <a href="lin.li.1@warwick.ac.uk">LIN LI</a>
                "." 
            </p>
            <h4>Who should I contact if I wish to make a complaint? </h4> 
            <p>
                "Any complaint should be addressed to the person below, who is a senior University of Warwick official entirely independent of this study:
                <a href="DPO@warwick.ac.uk"></a>
                "."
            </p>
            <div> 
